snippet: A prosecution witness in the sentencing phase of Pfc. Bradley Manning’s court-martial said that Al Qaeda could have used WikiLeaks disclosures to encourage attacks in the West.
abstract: Pentagon adviser Cmdr Youssef Aboul-Enein, who is witness for the prosecution in sentencing phase of court-martial of Pfc Bradley Manning, offers testimony saying Al Qaeda could have used WikiLeaks disclosures to encourage attacks on the West.
lead_paragraph: A prosecution witness in the sentencing phase of Pfc. Bradley Manning’s court-martial said that Al Qaeda could have used WikiLeaks disclosures to encourage attacks in the West.

headline.main: Witness in Manning Case Says Leaks Could Help Al Qaeda
